[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man accused over Bristol and North Somerset ATM blasts

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged in connection with cash machine explosions in Bristol and North Somerset.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Kyle Robert Joyner, of Wroughton Drive, Hartcliffe, Bristol, has been charged with conspiracy to steal, between 10 April and 5 May.
The 22-year-old was detained on Friday following recent attacks on ATMs in the area. Seven machines have been attacked since the start of the year.
He was remanded to appear before Bristol Magistrates' Court later.
